<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1982-05-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1982-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="23" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d23">
                        <head>23. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security
                            Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_WPClark2_1">Clark</persName>) to
                            President Reagan<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d23fn1">Source:
                                National Security Council, National Security Council Institutional
                                Files, Box SR 078, <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> 36 [<gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss> Negotiations II]. Secret. Sent
                                for action. Prepared by <persName corresp="#p_SKraemer_1">Kraemer</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_RLinhard_1">Linhard</persName>. A stamped notation at the top of the
                                memorandum reads: “signed.”</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1982-05-24">May 24, 1982</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <list type="subject">
                            <head>SUBJECT</head>
                            <item>Additional Guidance on <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss></item>
                        </list>
                        <p rend="sectiontitleital">Issue</p>
                        <p>Should you issue an <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> reflecting the
                            decisions reached as a result of the May 21 <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> meeting<note n="2" xml:id="d23fn2">See <ref target="#d21">Document 21</ref>.</note> on <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss>?</p>
                        <p rend="sectiontitleital">Facts</p>
                        <p>The <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> meeting on May 21 provides the
                            basis for you to issue additional guidance on the U.S. <gloss target="#t_START_1">START</gloss> position.</p>
                        <p rend="sectiontitleital">Discussion</p>
                        <p>Formalizing your decisions as a result of that meeting in an <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss>, will best ensure their clear
                            transmission and timely implementation.</p>
                        <p rend="sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
                        <table cols="3">
                            <row>
                                <cell><hi rend="roman">OK</hi></cell>
                                <cell><hi rend="roman">NO</hi></cell>
                                <cell/>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>________</cell>
                                <cell>________</cell>
                                <cell><hi rend="roman">That you approve and sign for release the
                                        proposed <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> at Tab
                                        A.</hi><note n="3" xml:id="d23fn3">Reagan initialed his
                                        approval. The <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> is
                                        printed below as <ref target="#d24">Document
                                        24</ref>.</note></cell>
                            </row>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>